		(uuid "fb3a6763-6f52-4876-a6c3-a6a58e7272d9")
	)
	(text "TOUCH_RESET always high to enable the chip."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -43.942 61.214 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right)
		)
		(uuid "fe96ed86-b998-4a69-8132-0f500de8491f")
	)
	(text_box "ESP32-S3 strapping pins:\n* GPIO0 weak pull-up, default 1 (boot mode selection)\n* GPIO3 floating (for JTAG control, unused if not burning efuses)\n* GPIO45 weak pull-down, default 0 (VDD_SPI voltage control, should be left default 0)\n* GPIO46 weak pull-down, default 0 (also boot mode selection, we always want it 0 at startup)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 227.33 20.32 0)
		(size 49.53 13.97)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "07302b45-17f5-40a9-b307-7dc77713dc57")
	)
	(text_box "I2C addresses used:\n\n0011000 - accelerometer\n0101100 - USB Hub\n1110xxx - GPIO expanders\n0011xxx - I2C multiplexers\n0010xxx - ADC expanders"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 123.19 114.3 0)
		(size 44.45 30.48)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1293e6ea-ea78-4963-8782-4b4824e0ae38")
	)
	(text_box "Hex Master\n\nThis circuit board has WiFi connectivity and controls 24 Hex Mini Servos \nvia the SPI bus.\n* ESP32-S3 as main control processor with WiFi and Bluetooth.\n* CAN bus for external motors, onwards connection.\n* 2 I2C connectors for sensor boards.\n* Touch Screen for setup and manual controls.\n* USB for programming/config.\n* Host USB for sensor suite.\n\nTODO:\n[v] BOOT0 pull up is too weak, need our own.\n[ ] Need to talk to usb hub via the main USB PHY.\n[v] Implement the Auto-Program Circuit: Connect \nthe CP2102N RTS and DTR lines to the standard \ndual-transistor reset network (driving EN and GPIO 0).\n[ ] Search for a display again...\n[ ] Maybe look for cheaper MOSFET high side gate driver\n[ ] Do we want analog expanders to measure individual currents?\n[ ] Gate the I2C chips behind the multiplexer cause we have the 1 or 2 spare outputs.\n[ ] Single current sense for VBUS and VBATTERY, with the other 7 sensors for \nthe 7 device power. Use the beefier sense for vcc. Also need about 3.5-4mm trace widths.\n[ ] 2 oz copper!\n[ ] Pull downs on the VBUS and VBATTERY connect lines.\n[ ] Switch to more common display with pins, this time we should find where to buy it reliably."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 16.51 15.4631 0)
		(size 102.87 71.9358)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.5 1.5)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1f2cd93c-8b7e-4e68-aa3b-015869c6a291")
	)
	(text_box "CAN Slope control. This 10k resistor slightly slows down the level transition."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 529.59 311.15 0)
		(size 41.91 5.08)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "5b68271f-a804-4755-ab36-ddf68605934a")
	)
	(text_box "Servo connectors with USB-C and power via FPC\n\nEach hierarchical component represents a pair of USB-C and FPC connectors\nfor a downstream device.\n\nThe NRST and BOOT0 wires can be connected either way and also double\nas I2C connectors for further multiplexing downstream devices. We\nneed to connect them to the GPIO and I2C multiplexers. They will have\nthe following options:\n	1. The STM32 servo drivers will have a pull-up on NRST and pull-down on BOOT0.\n	We will use the GPIO multiplexer to first read the values to determine the plug\n	orientation then we can toggle the lines to enter the bootloader mode to upload\n	code without the device ever being programmed.\n	2. If both lines are pulled up then we have connected a downstream multiplexer.\n	Test out which way the connection works by attempting an I2C transaction; note\n	send some blank data in order to reset the data lines if we have guessed wrong.\n	3. If both lines are pulled down, then it's probably not our device."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -90.17 -376.2477 0)
		(size 107.95 36.6624)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "64ee41d2-56b2-475c-bcd8-6734f041c47e")
	)
	(text_box "I2C address for touch screen is: 0x15 / 0b00010101"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
